about.body: This 3.5 San Francisco Chronicle rated and four-year running Michelin Starred Restaurant is a follow up to Mourad Lahlou's Michelin starred Aziza. Mourad is a modern interpretation of a cuisine deeply rooted in the past. Our food pays homage to those roots, showcasing the rich and vibrant flavors of Morocco in new ways that harmonize with the fresh, local, artisanal ingredients, and the spirit of innovation of Northern California. Mourad is located in the historic Pacific Bell building in San Francisco’s South of Market and Financial Districts. The contemporary design seamlessly blends the Art Deco building with steel accents for a setting that is both modern and inviting.

We gladly accept reservations online up to 60 days in advance for parties of up to 6 guests comprised of no more than 2 households per City of San Francisco COVID regulations. 

For parties of 8 or more, please contact our Events Director at events@mouradsf.com ( special events for large parties are not available until the COVID restrictions are lifted)

Our bar and lounge table are available for walk-in guests. Seating on these areas is closed during COVID

If you are running late, please call the restaurant at (415) 660-2500. We hold the table for a grace period of 15 minutes.

about.body: A local favorite and San Francisco culinary institution since 2003, Town Hall showcases its classic southern indulgences - Fried Chicken, BBQ shrimp, St. Louis Ribs paired with a chilled Bacon-Bourbon Old Fashioned or Classic Sazerac. Exciting new menu additions will also be offered as a tribute to the recent and permanent closure of K- Paul’s Louisiana Kitchen, the 40 year old famed southern restaurant founded by the late, legendary Chef Paul Prudhomme – a mentor to Chef/Owner Mitchell Rosenthal.

need_to_know.body: Reservations are highly recommended. Walk-ins are always welcomed. There is free street parking after 6pm and on weekends in addition a parking structure on Mission St.  between 1st & 2nd and a lot on Howard St between 1st & 2nd.

about.body:
Nestled within Rincon Hill, Local Kitchen & Wine Merchant has introduced a rustic, intercontinental style of dining to the bustling neighborhood. Our menu—featuring Singaporean-inspired fare from Chef Nora Haron, in addition to our famous wood-fired pizzas—is a mouth-watering love letter to curated flavors, expertly executed. Desserts, too, are created in the same fashion; never too sweet, leveraging natural sugars and high-quality ingredients. 

Our mantra, sweet or savory? Keep it simple—and do it well. 

Behind the bar, you’ll find a creative cocktail menu that pulls inspiration from top-notch spirits, crafted with tongue-in-cheek nods to pop-culture and local landmarks. Beer taps, featuring regional brews, and, as you’d expect, an impeccable wine list round-out our 21-and-over offerings.

Located on 1st Street, between Folsom and Harrison, we’re only a short jot from San Francisco landmarks—but offer flavors you’d need a stamped passport to macerate.

need_to_know.body: Although we’re more than happy to take any-and-all reservation, of any size, we appreciate a heads-up for parties of 9 or more. Regardless, come in, and we’ll find a seat (or seats) for you.

about.body:
Sushi Nagai is located at 125 Ellis Street in San Francisco’s bustling Union Square neighborhood. The serene traditional dining room has 20 seats and is helmed by Chef Tomonori Nagai, whose specialty is Edomae-style sushi. Nagai started his career as a sushi chef in Japan in the 1990s, after graduating from the Musashino Culinary School in Tokyo. He worked as a sushi chef at Sushiden in Japan and its New York City outpost. One of his proudest moments was serving Pres. Barack Obama while working as sushi chef at Morimoto, Hawaii. Nagai also worked at Shinji by Kanesaka, a Michelin star restaurant in Singapore.

Sushi Nagai is nightly for dinner from 6:00pm – 11:00pm and closed on Mondays. Reservations are highly recommended. Walk-ins are accommodated on a case-by-case basis depending on additional product availability that evening. For more information, visit www.sushinagaisf.com.

need_to_know.body:
Currently Sushi Nagai is offering two To-Go menus:

バラちらし
Chirashi Sushi Bowl, $80
Sashimi and vegetables on a bed of sushi rice.
Chef Nagai has selected Anago (Conger Eel), Tuna, Kohada (Gizzard Shad), Tai (Red Snapper), Ikura (salmon roe), Uni (sea urchin), and Tamago Yaki (egg omelette), scattered over his signature sushi rices (two different Koshihikari rice seasoned with two different red vinegars from Chiba and Tokyo). 

Unagi Don $50
Fresh water eel with pickled ginger and seaweed, in Nagai's signature rice box. 

We encourage our guests to enjoy the meals as soon as possible, ideally within one hour of pick up. 

At Sushi Nagai, we always strive to have the most excellent standards of service in the preparation of our cuisine and in hosting our guests. We are now taking even further precautions during the current temperature surrounding COVID-19 in order to protect our patrons, staff, and community. This includes routinely following the guidelines set by the World Health Organization and the Center of Disease Control. 

Further, we are encouraging guests to use chopsticks while enjoying our food and are taking scrupulous measures for sanitizing doorknobs and handle bars. 

Our goal is to maintain a safe and comfortable environment for our guest in the coming of weeks. We are also happy to assist with rescheduling of any upcoming reservations. We will continue to monitor any updates and news in regards to best practices. Should you have further questions or concerns, please reach out to sushinagaisf@gmail.com.

Chef Tomonori Nagai utilizes the highest quality fish from Japan alongside local California ingredients. Chef Nagai serves three different omakase menus each evening, which combine several sushi courses along with small, seasonally focused dishes. 

Please make note of our cancellation policy. Due to the nature of our menu, we require all cancellations within 72 hours of the reservation date to incur a $200 charge per person. If you fail to arrive for your reservation you will be charged the full price of the menu. 

Street parking can be difficult, we recommend car share or public transportation to the restaurant. The closest BART station is at Powell and Market. If driving, the closest parking lot is the Ellis O’Farrell Garage (across from Macy’s). 

For same day reservations, please call the restaurant directly at 415.319.5268.

We look forward to welcoming you to Sushi Nagai!

Ni- 18 courses, including sushi and small plates. Additional supplemental a la carte pieces available.
San- 18 courses, including sushi and small plates highlighting premium ingredients. Additional supplemental a la carte pieces available.

content.body: Wine flights are a great way to learn about wine. You can compare a French Sancerre to its California cousin Sauvignon Blanc and note its nuances. Allow SF Wine Society to help. There’s also cheese, charcuterie, and caviar to pair while you’re at it.
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body:
At San Francisco Wine Society we celebrate classic wines from classic regions and enjoy introducing our guests to intriguing wines from every corner of the globe. Featuring a different region each month allows us to guide our guests on a journey of time and place.

Our front patio features two fireplaces to keep you warm and cozy on those chilly San Francisco nights. Our back patio has a bocce court to encourage a competitive, yet playful spirit! 

We look forward to welcoming you.

San Francisco Wine Society is a woman owned business.

need_to_know.body:
We hold the table for a grace period of 15 minutes before offering the reservation to our waitlist. If you are running late, please call us at (415) 674-3567. 

As much as we love animals, our patios are not pet friendly. We kindly ask that you leave your fury friends at home.

We are a 21 and over only establishment. By law we are not able to make any exceptions, including for infants. Thank you for understanding.

content.body: Mister Jiu’s is a testament to the best of Chinese family-style dining (from the flashy gold lotus chandeliers to the indoor tables’ built-in lazy susans) with a Bay Area sensibility that just works. It has redefined Chinese American food in America, and we absolutely love it.
content.name: why_we_like_it
content.title: Why We Like It

about.body: With its mid-century furniture and minimalist style, Mister Jiu’s isn’t your typical Chinese joint. Chinese-American chef Brandon Jew’s first solo venture delivers some classic Cantonese dishes with a Bay Area twist, all crowned with a Michelin star. Funny story: Mister Jiu’s lives in the former space of an old Chinese banquet hall chef Jew loved as a child.

tagline.body: Moongate Lounge located in historic San Francisco Chinatown above Mister Jiu's

about.body:
The Moongate Lounge is a 55 seat cocktail bar and lounge with an 80 seat event space above Mister Jiu’s restaurant in San Francisco Chinatown. 

The cocktail list at Moongate Lounge will have 6 house cocktails named after moons in our solar system and 6 seasonally rotating cocktails named after the Chinese lunar calendar. Each of the cocktails take inspiration from Chinese ingredients, but are structurally built from classic cocktail recipes. Another feature to the cocktail program will be the ‘bottle service’, which will feature hard to find, exceptional and allocated spirits served by the ounce. 

The food menu will be focused on hors d’oeuvres, bar snacks and Chef Brandon Jew’s interpretation of some Chinese American throwbacks like: Bakkwa, Pig Trotter Ham Sui Gok, Parisian 'Egg Tart', and more!

The wines are exclusively focused on natural wines and pivots toward affordable, delicious, and unique options that will compliment the food menu. The wine list will rotate, but all wines selected will be from vineyards farmed using organic and/or biodynamic practices with no additions in the wine, other than little to no sulphur. Just as we care about the farming practices for our food, we feel the same about the wines being poured at the Moongate Lounge. The majority of the wines range between $40-100 per bottle.

about.body:
Verjus is a neighborhood restaurant, wine bar, and retail shop in the heart of downtown San Francisco’s Jackson Square. Alongside housemade charcuterie, artisanal cheeses, fish conserva, and organic produce from our own Fresh Run Farm, Chef Michael Tusk offers a weekly changing menu of inventive riffs on bistro classics—all driven by the best of the season and our local purveyors’ daily picks.

We’re as passionate (read: obsessive) about wine as we are about food, focusing on small-scale, independent growers farming organically and making wines with minimal additives. Whether you’re seeking out a quirky cult bottle or a coveted vintage from the world’s most celebrated vignerons, our team will ensure you drink exceptionally well at any price point.

You’ll find us here Tuesday through Saturday, come say hello at the wine shop or check out our current favorites online for pickup or delivery.

And if you can’t get enough of natural wine, join our Verjus Vivants wine club to receive our selections of the most dynamic, intriguing bottlings each month.

need_to_know.title: Need to Know
need_to_know.body: Verjus will be hibernating (sort of….) for the winter months. Due to Covid-related service restrictions, we’ve decided to pause regular service for the remainder of the calendar year.  To celebrate the holiday season, we’ll be hosting a series of events – from a pig roast to a Dungeness crab boil – all outdoors and safely, socially distanced (stay tuned for more details)!

about.body: The immersive world of Boulettes Larder is an insider's favorite: the most elegant, organic,  and ethical restaurant experience in the Ferry Building Marketplace.   Amaryll Schwertner and Lori Regis offer a warm welcome that engages all the senses.   Chef Schwertner combines her love for the best Northern California farm ingredients with her wide-ranging knowledge of global foodways, flavors, and aromas.  In a space that feels as personal as a private kitchen, Boulettes Larder is 'farm-to-table' at its most alive.

content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body:
Angler is a sea-life focused restaurant from Chef Joshua Skenes and Saison Hospitality.

Each day’s inspiration is drawn from the products themselves and is an articulation of their natural flavors served at their peak taste. We work with a small group of fishermen, hunters, gatherers, ranchers, and farmers to find and follow microclimates that produce the highest quality products in local existence. All of the cooking revolves around an open wood fire.

Thank you and we look forward to seeing you!

content.body: This is a beloved pizzeria with an impressive backstory: The oven that’s dishing out charred and chewy Neapolitan pies was previously housed in a truck that roved the streets of San Francisco.
content.name: why_we_like_it

about.body:
Having slung his top-notch Neapolitan pizzas from a specially rigged, wood-oven-equipped truck for several years, local pizzaiolo Jon Darsky opened this lower Nob Hill spot four years ago, and now has two Michelin Bib Gourmand listing under his belt. While it's easily some of the best pizza in the city, the menu also boasts Chef Jeffrey Hayden's seasonally, market-driven changing appetizers and small plates.
This version of Del Popolo offers a more expansive menu but with the same attention to detail and thoughtfulness that has always formed the core of our approach to making pizza.
Inspiration derives from our various dining experiences, as well as from the farms and ranches in our midst.

about.body: Hog Island Oyster Bar in San Francisco, located in the historic San Francisco Ferry Building, offers the finest selection of oysters, craft cocktails, and an ever-changing seasonal menu that features seafood fresh off the boats and produce plucked from the local Farmers’ Markets. Enjoy Hog Island’s finest while looking out over San Francisco Bay, the Bay Bridge, and Treasure Island.  Hog Island San Francisco does not currently accept reservations and all seating for the restaurant is via waitlist

content.name: why_we_like_it

tagline.body: Owl craft beer on tap & wagyu beef bites by Chef Noriyuki Sugie.

about.body: Hitachino Beer and Wagyu is the first iteration of Kiuchi Brewery's set of tap houses. Beer, sake, and wine are made by Kiuchi (based in Konosu, Japan and est. in 1823), while chef-owner Noriyuki Sugie is behind the omakase, bar food program, and a la carte menu focused around Japanese A5 Wagyu from Hitachi, US Wagyu from Nebraska, and other local, seasonal ingredients. The restaurant's interior includes table tops made with cherry blossom barrels used to age sake, giving Hitachino the same feel of the brewery in Japan.

why_we_like_it.body: Wagyu beef gets the tail-to-nose treatment at this establishment, backed by the legendary Kiuchi Brewery. That means the greatest A5 cuts are accompanied by the finest Japanese beer, and there’s no better way to savor the prized meat.
